==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hittorf tube
<hw>Hit"torf tube</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A highly
exhausted glass tube with metallic electrodes nearly in contact so as to
exhibit the insulating effects of a vacuum. It was used by the German
physicist <person>W. Hittorf</person> (b. 1824).</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A Crookes tube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hive</ent>⟦br⟧
